        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I'm aware that this is a request for NewPipe itself and that requests for adding a new service need to be made at [NewPipeExtractor](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipeExtractor/issues).\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the feature request will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one feature request.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Feature description\n\nYoutube has recently started letting (some) movies be shown on youtube, complete & \"Free with ads\". However, there is a _minor_ problem with _playing_ such videos.\r\n\r\nI only have an android tablet (Android 11, not rooted) & I use 3 browsers on it (Chrome, 1dm+, & X-Browser).\r\nIf you go to one of these youtube movies on an _android_ phone/tablet in a BROWSER using the MOBILE version of that youtube movie's URL (example = https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=ZhHRh_1ufnI) you'll see this message.\r\n**This content can't be played on your mobile browser. Get the YouTube app to start watching.**\r\nIf you paste that URL into NewPipe's search bar & go to it, you'll see this message.\r\n**Sorry, something went wrong.** (with a giant sad emoticon face)\r\nIf you go to that URL in a browser & choose \"Desktop mode\" in your browser & then refresh the page, it will change the URL into this (https://www.youtube.com/watch?app=desktop&v=ZhHRh_1ufnI) & you'll be able to play the video.\r\n\r\nThe problem (for NewPipe) is that either there is not a way to do that, or if there is, I haven't found it. Therefore, I request that NewPipe should be given a way to play such videos. It seems like a solution could be as simple as adding a \"Desktop mode\" option to it.\n\n### Why do you want this feature?\n\nI'll add that for most of the youtube movies I can find most of them somewhere else. However, _those_ sites are always getting taken down, whereas youtube is not in danger of that happening. Therefore, watching/downloading those specific movies would be made more doable if NewPipe gets this requested feature.\n\n### Additional information\n\n_No response_",
