        "body": "### Checklist\n\n- [X] I am able to reproduce the bug with the latest version given here: [CLICK THIS LINK](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/releases/latest).\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the bug report will be dismissed otherwise.\n- [X] This issue contains only one bug.\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\n\n### Affected version\n\n0.25.2\n\n### Steps to reproduce the bug\n\n1) Start NewPipe as normal.\r\n2) Paste one of the video URLs into NewPipe & press the \"Return\" button on my (on screen) keyboard.\r\n(The video URLs are located below.)\r\n3) Newpipe will go to that video's youtube \"page\".\r\n4) Press the \"Play\" button to _try_ to play the video.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe expected behavior is that NewPipe should be able to play the videos that I have included links to. Also, I cannot say if this problem occured (or not) in previous versions of NewPipe because I only found the videos recently.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nIf you follow the \"Steps to reproduce the bug\" (see that section above), then if you _try_ to play one of the videos, the video will NOT play. Instead, I get the following error message.\r\n**\"An error occurred, see the notification\"**\r\nThe notification message is this.\r\n**\"NewPipe encountered an error, tap to report\r\nUnrecoverable player error occurred\"**\r\n\r\nThis does _not_ cause any other problems using NewPipe (example = doing this does not make NewPipe crash), & NewPipe (0.25.2) IS able to play _most_ youtube videos without any problem, but the following youtube videos experience the bug that I'm reporting.\r\n\r\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/cl9LZiB0oao/maxresdefault.jpg\r\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/FX4t1lLNl-o/maxresdefault.jpg\r\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/otNh9bTjXWg/maxresdefault.jpg\r\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/RDE6Uz73A7g/maxresdefault.jpg\r\nhttps://i.ytimg.com/vi/vOl1uBC3sjs/maxresdefault.jpg\r\n\r\nFor some reason involving a serious design FAILURE, NewPipe does NOT have a way to give me a youtube video's URL. Instead, I can only get the URL for their THUMBNAILS (from NewPipe). However, I know how to _convert_ those into youtube VIDEO URLs, so here they are.\r\n\r\nhttps://m.youtube.com/watch?v=cl9LZiB0oao\r\nhttps://m.youtube.com/watch?v=FX4t1lLNl-o\r\nhttps://m.youtube.com/watch?v=otNh9bTjXWg\r\nhttps://m.youtube.com/watch?v=RDE6Uz73A7g\r\nhttps://m.youtube.com/watch?v=vOl1uBC3sjs\r\n\r\nI have tried both using & not using a VPN with those videos, but it doesn't help NewPipe play them. I found a similar topic in the \"Issues\" section (https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues/9255), but it said that it was probably related to their specific WIFI, so I doubt that the same is true for me because I only use _one_ WIFI, & all of these _all_ of these videos DO work in _browsers_ on that WIFI.\n\n### Screenshots/Screen recordings\n\n_No response_\n\n### Logs\n\n_No response_\n\n### Affected Android/Custom ROM version\n\nAndroid 11 (not rooted, came with the device)\n\n### Affected device model\n\nSamsung Galaxy Tab A7\n\n### Additional information\n\nIf more information from me is wanted or needed, ask & I'll provide it. I'll check on this at least once a day, so expect a delay in getting a response from me. Also, adding a way to get a youtube video's URL would be helpful for many reasons (example = bug reports).",
