        "body": "### Checklist\r\n\r\n- [X] I am able to reproduce the bug with the latest version given here: [CLICK THIS LINK](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/releases/latest).\r\n- [X] I made sure that there are *no existing issues* - [open](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues) or [closed](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/issues?q=is%3Aissue+is%3Aclosed) - which I could contribute my information to.\r\n- [X] I have read the [FAQ](https://newpipe.net/FAQ/) and my problem isn't listed.\r\n- [X] I have taken the time to fill in all the required details. I understand that the bug report will be dismissed otherwise.\r\n- [X] This issue contains only one bug.\r\n- [X] I have read and understood the [contribution guidelines](https://github.com/TeamNewPipe/NewPipe/blob/dev/.github/CONTRIBUTING.md).\r\n\r\n### Affected version\r\n\r\n0.25.2\r\n\r\n### Steps to reproduce the bug\r\n\r\nSimple, download something, pause it, close the app or open any other apps until it causes newpipe to refresh itself on open (or if it crashes too). Go to downloads. Find your paused download gone.\r\n______________________________\r\nSo if there is a download and the user decides to pause it, why the fuck does the app auto-deletes what's paused from the downloads list if the app is closed, refreshed due to low ram etc OR oh lord it CRASHES because it's mega buggy (to the point that it's funny how some high priority bugs are left unaddressed)? That's just stupid, really stupid.. It would be pretty nice if it DIDN'T do that, causing the user to have to redownload the entire video FROM SCRATCH.\r\n\r\nAlso uh when will those 1.2k open issue reports get addressed? Seems to me like at this point it's better to just use Youtube and move on from using newpipe if y'all just abandoned it causing anyother fork to be stalled too because ya can't be bothered to just give the reigns to somebody else really.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nNot getting my shit deleted if i close the app, it is forcefully refreshed due to other apps hogging the ram or god forbid this buggy piece of software doesn't crash from simply doing basic things\r\n\r\n### Actual behavior\r\n\r\nAs explained before, download gets wiped if it's a paused one.\r\nFix this shit. Who tf thought it was a brilliant idea?\r\n\r\n### Screenshots/Screen recordings\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Logs\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Affected Android/Custom ROM version\r\n\r\nAny\r\n\r\n### Affected device model\r\n\r\nAny\r\n\r\n### Additional information\r\n\r\n_No response_",
